INSERT INTO skills (name, description, category, command, common, content, is_deleted) VALUES (
  'api-design',
  'REST/HTTP API design patterns â€” resource naming, status codes, pagination, filtering, errors, versioning, idempotency. Use when designing or reviewing API endpoints.',
  'craft',
  NULL,
  0,
  '# api-design â€” designing & reviewing HTTP APIs

## Resources & methods
- Name resources as **plural nouns**, never verbs: `/users`, `/users/{id}/orders`.
- `GET` read (safe, idempotent) Â· `POST` create / non-idempotent action Â·
  `PUT` full replace (idempotent) Â· `PATCH` partial update Â· `DELETE` remove.
- Nest one level deep max; beyond that, link by id.

## Status codes
- `200` ok Â· `201` created (+ `Location`) Â· `204` no content.
- `400` bad input Â· `401` unauth Â· `403` forbidden Â· `404` not found Â·
  `409` conflict Â· `422` validation Â· `429` rate-limited.
- `5xx` = server''s fault; NEVER return `5xx` for a client error.

## Payloads
- One error shape everywhere: `{ "error": { "code", "message", "details" } }`.
- **Pagination**: cursor-based for large/changing sets (`?cursor=&limit=`),
  return `next_cursor`; offset only for small stable sets.
- **Filtering/sorting**: explicit query params (`?status=open&sort=-created`);
  whitelist fields â€” NEVER interpolate them into a query.
- Timestamps ISO-8601 UTC; ids opaque strings.

## Robustness
- **Idempotency**: make retries safe â€” `PUT`/`DELETE` naturally; for `POST`,
  accept an idempotency key.
- **Versioning**: prefix (`/v1/â€¦`) or header; add fields backward-compatibly,
  never repurpose an existing one.
- Validate at the boundary; unknown fields = reject or ignore â€” pick one and
  document it. NEVER leak internals (stack traces, SQL) in error responses.

## Review lens
Each endpoint does one thing? Right method + status? Errors uniform? Inputs
validated/whitelisted? Retries safe? Breaking change hiding in a "small"
tweak?',
  0
)
