INSERT INTO skills (name, description, category, command, common, content, is_deleted) VALUES (
  'windows_devkit',
  'Drive the linked Windows Test VM â€” push a build artifact, exec the installer/test over SSH, capture output + a screenshot, then reset to the clean snapshot. High-fidelity installer/system-level testing where Wine is useless. Use when building or verifying Windows software in a fork that has a configured VM.',
  'substrate',
  NULL,
  0,
  '# windows_devkit â€” driving the Windows Test VM

Real Windows, for the testing Wine can''t fake: MSI installers, services, the
registry, system-level behavior. Opt-in + link-only â€” the operator runs the
VM; you drive a verified loop against it. Devs build + test; the reviewer
independently verifies the dev''s candidate artifact with exec â†’ capture â†’
reset. Grant is explicit, per-fork (`common=0`).

## Precondition â€” the link is configured

VM config = `vm` key in `.super-coder/instance.json` (set via the GUI Scripts
â†’ **Windows Test VM** wizard, which live-tests every field before save):

```json
"vm": { "domain": "win-test", "ssh_host": "127.0.0.1", "ssh_port": 22,
        "ssh_user": "tester", "ssh_key_path": "~/.ssh/sc_win_test",
        "transfer_dir": "/var/sc/win-xfer", "snapshot": "clean",
        "libvirt_uri": "qemu:///system" }
```

`libvirt_uri` optional â€” set it when the domain is system-scope (the default
`qemu:///session` can''t see it); omit otherwise.

- No `vm` block â†’ no VM linked: stop + ask the operator to run the wizard.
- `configure_winbox` must also have run, or the box has no toolchain â€” the
  wizard''s `toolchain` check confirms it did.
- A wrong field â†’ fix it in the wizard (it re-validates); NEVER hand-edit
  secrets into config.
- `ssh_key_path` = a path, never key material. Never read it â€” the key lives
  host-side with the broker (below).

## Drive through the host broker â€” never ssh/virsh directly

You run inside the sandbox; the VM lives on the host''s libvirt NAT,
unreachable from here, and the container has no `ssh`, no `virsh`, no key.
Call the host-side **vm-broker** over its unix socket in the bind-mounted
repo; the broker holds the key + libvirt. (Detail:
`.super-coder/docs/windows-vm-broker.md`.)

```bash
SOCK="$(sc vm-broker-sock)"
curl -s --unix-socket "$SOCK" http://vm/health      # liveness check first
```

curl fails "not reachable" â†’ broker down â†’ ask the operator to run
`sc vm-broker-up` on the host. You cannot start it yourself (host process,
not sandbox).

## The loop â€” push â†’ exec â†’ capture â†’ reset

Every run starts from the clean snapshot â€” without the reset, installer
side-effects leak between runs and the next result is a lie.

| Verb | Call |
|---|---|
| **push** | `curl -s --unix-socket "$SOCK" http://vm/push -d ''{"src":"<repo path to artifact>"}''` â€” stages into `transfer_dir` (the guest''s share) |
| **exec** | `curl -s --unix-socket "$SOCK" http://vm/exec -d ''{"command":"<installer / test cmd>"}''` â†’ `{ok, exit, stdout, stderr}` |
| **capture** | `curl -s --unix-socket "$SOCK" http://vm/capture -d ''{"command":"<optional cmd>"}''` â†’ stdout + a base64 `virsh screenshot` for GUI state |
| **reset** (start) | `curl -s --unix-socket "$SOCK" http://vm/reset -X POST` â€” revert to clean + **boot** |
| **reset** (done) | `curl -s --unix-socket "$SOCK" http://vm/reset -d ''{"running":false}''` â€” revert to clean, leave **powered OFF** |

The broker runs ssh non-interactively from the saved `vm` block â€” name a
command, never a host or a key.

**Bracket every run with reset.** Start with `/reset` (boots a clean box);
end â€” even on failure â€” with `/reset {"running":false}` (clean + powered off:
an idle running VM pins ~12 GB of host RAM). The clean snapshot is OFFLINE
(this CPU''s non-migratable `invtsc` flag refuses a live snapshot), so a bare
revert lands powered-off; `{"running":true}` (the default) boots it â€”
`{"running":false}` gets clean **and** off in a single op.

## Stance

- **You drive, you don''t provision.** Missing toolchain â†’ admin''s
  `configure_winbox` + re-bake. NEVER `winget install` from this loop â€” it
  poisons the clean snapshot.
- **The reviewer verifies, doesn''t build.** Reviewer runs exec â†’ capture â†’
  reset on the dev''s candidate artifact to confirm the claim independently.',
  0
)
